# The Nucleus · The dense core: protons and neutrons packed by the strong force into a ball ~100,000 times smaller than the atom, holding nearly all its mass at ~10¹⁷ kg/m³ (a sugar-cube of it would weigh ~billions of tonnes).

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

